# Privacy Policy for RouteVista

**Last Updated: April 18, 2026**

Rajnish Sinh ("we," "our," or "us") operates the RouteVista mobile application. This page informs you of our policies regarding the collection, use, and disclosure of personal data when you use our Service and the choices you have associated with that data.

## 1. Information Collection and Use
We collect several different types of information for various purposes to provide and improve our Service to you.

### Types of Data Collected
- **Personal Data**: While using our Service, we may ask you to provide us with certain personally identifiable information that can be used to contact or identify you, including your Email address, First name, and Last name (via Firebase Authentication).
- **Location Data**: RouteVista requires access to your precise location data to provide turn-by-turn navigation and discover nearby points of interest. This data is processed locally and via trusted geocoding services (like OpenStreetMap).
- **Chat History**: We collect and store your interactions with the RouteVista AI assistant to provide conversation context and improve the AI's helpfulness.

## 2. Use of Data
RouteVista uses the collected data for various purposes:
- To provide and maintain the Service (including navigation and offline maps).
- To allow you to participate in interactive features of our Service (AI Chatbot).
- To provide customer support and manage user accounts.
- To detect, prevent, and address technical issues.

## 3. Third-Party Service Providers
We may employ third-party companies and individuals to facilitate our Service. These third parties have access to your Data only to perform these tasks on our behalf:
- **Google Firebase**: For user authentication and cloud database synchronization.
- **AI Providers (Gemini/Groq)**: To process your queries within the chatbot assistant.
- **OpenStreetMap & Nominatim**: For map rendering and search services.

## 4. Data Security
The security of your data is important to us, but remember that no method of transmission over the Internet or method of electronic storage is 100% secure. We use Firebase's industry-standard security protocols to protect your information.

## 5. Your Data Protection Rights
You have the right to:
- Access, update, or delete the information we have on you.
- Withdraw your consent at any time where we relied on your consent to process your personal information.

## 6. Children's Privacy
Our Service does not address anyone under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personally identifiable information from anyone under the age of 13.

## 7. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page.

